 </p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Golden Hour" /><category term="Temples" /><category term="Aerial" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Looking north on Karasuma Dori, with Higashi Honganji Temple in front and the northern mountains in the distance.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2024/2410_A7R07426_ai.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2024/2410_A7R07426_ai.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Ginza Line・銀座線</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/241019/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Ginza Line・銀座線" /><published>2024-10-19T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2024-10-19T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/ginza-line</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/241019/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Slow exposure at the Shibuya Station of Tokyo’s Ginza Line subway. Shot on Ilford HP5 film.
</p>

<p class="jp">
東京の銀座線渋谷駅でのスローシャッター。イルフォード HP5フィルムで撮影。
 </p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Tokyo" /><category term="Black and White" /><category term="Film" /><category term="Long Exposure" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Slow exposure at the Shibuya Station of Tokyo’s Ginza Line subway. Shot on Ilford HP5 film.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2024/2410_A7R07357.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2024/2410_A7R07357.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Misty Morning・朝霧</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/241017/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Misty Morning・朝霧" /><published>2024-10-17T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2024-10-17T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/yusai</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/241017/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Mist emanating from Atelier Yusai as I was walking by this morning. Maybe its another special effect like at <a href="/240602/">Ninna-ji Temple</a> this spring. Those are Yusai's hanging textiles.
</p>

<p class="jp">
今朝、通りかかった際にアトリエ祐斎から立ち上る霧。もしかしたら、今年の春に<a href="/240602/">仁和寺</a>で見たような特別な効果があるのかもしれない。吊るされたテキスタイルは祐斎氏によるもの。
 </p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Fog" /><category term="Art" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Mist emanating from Atelier Yusai as I was walking by this morning. Maybe its another special effect like at Ninna-ji Temple this spring. Those are Yusai's hanging textiles.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2024/2410_A7R07264.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2024/2410_A7R07264.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Ishibunebashi Bridge・石船橋</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/241015/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Ishibunebashi Bridge・石船橋" /><published>2024-10-15T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2024-10-15T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/ishibunebashi</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/241015/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
This picturesque footbridge is at a bend in the Minamiaki River, in Akigawa Valley at the extreme west end of Tokyo.
</p>

<p class="jp">
この絵のように美しい歩道橋は、東京の最西端にある秋川渓谷の南秋川の曲がり角にある。
 </p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Tokyo" /><category term="Bridges" /><category term="Rivers" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[This picturesque footbridge is at a bend in the Minamiaki River, in Akigawa Valley at the extreme west end of Tokyo.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2024/2410_A7R07208.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2024/2410_A7R07208.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Kurochaya・黒茶屋</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/241014/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Kurochaya・黒茶屋" /><published>2024-10-14T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2024-10-14T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/kurochaya</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/241014/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
This is just a restaurant customer waiting area, but the round window with the paper <em>shoji</em> screen, and the hanging <em>jizaikagi</em> with a fish (usually hanging over a hearth) creates a serene Japanese feeling.
</p>
<p class="en">
<a href="https://kurochaya.com" target="_blank">Kurochaya</a>  is a Japanese restaurant in a 300 year old traditional home, along the Akigawa River in the western foothills of Tokyo, far from Tokyo Tower. 
</p>

<p class="jp">
これは、ただのレストランの待合室の写真ですが、丸い窓に和紙の障子があり、魚が飾られた自在鉤が掛かっていることで、静かな和の雰囲気が感じられます。
 </p>
 <p class="jp">
     <a href="https://kurochaya.com" target="_blank" >黒茶屋</a>は、東京タワーから遠く離れた東京の西の山麓、秋川沿いに位置する、300年の歴史を持つ古民家を利用した日本料理店です。
 </p>
